31; Pan, C.Y., Gas separation by permeators with high-flux asymmetric membranes (1983) AIChE Journal, 29, pp. 545-552; Taniguchi, I., Duan, S., Kazama, S., Fujioka, Y., Facile fabrication of a novel high performance CO2 separation membrane: Immobilization of poly(amidoamine) dendrimers in poly(ethylene glycol) networks (2008) Journal of Membrane Science, 322, pp. 277-280; Duan, S., Chowdhury, F.A., Kai, T., Kazama, S., Fujioka, Y., PAMAM dendrimer composite membrane for CO2 separation: addition of hyaluronic acid in gutter layer and application of novel hydroxyl PAMAM dendrimer (2008) Desalination, 234, pp. 278-285; Teramoto, M., Kitada, S., Ohnishi, N., Matsuyama, H., Matsumiya, N., Separation and concentration of CO2 by capillary-type facilitated transport membrane module with permeation of carrier solution (2004) Journal of Membrane Science, 234, pp. 83-94; Ward, W.J., Robb, W.L., Carbon dioxide-oxygen separation: facilitated transport of carbon dioxide across a liquid film (1967) Science, 156, pp. 1481-1484; Bhave, R.R., Sirkar, K.K.J., Gas permeation and separation by aqueous membranes immobilized across the whole thickness or in a thin section of hydrophobic microporous celgard films (1986) Journal of Membrane Science, 27, p. 41; (2005) Carbon Capture and Sequestration Systems Analysis Guideline, DOE/NETL; Lin, H., Merkel, T.C., Baker, R.W., The membrane solution to global warming (2007) Sixth Annual Conference on Carbon Capture & Sequestration; Baker, R.W., Wijmans, J.G., Merkel, T.C., Lin, H., Daniels, R., Thompson, S., (2009) Gas separation process using membranes with permeate sweep to remove CO2 from combustion gases, , Patent PCT/US2009/002874; Mikus, T., Melien, T., CO2 capture project: CCP economics overview (2004) Third Annual Conference on Carbon Capture and Sequestration; Zou, J., Ho, W.S.W., CO2-selective polymeric membranes containing amines in crosslinked poly(vinyl alcohol) (2006) Journal of Membrane Science, 286, pp. 310-321; Cai, Y., Wang, Z.,